The latest MSTest version is **4.2.2** (a major version bump). Here are the breaking changes that affect **your code specifically**:

### 1. `[ExpectedException]` is removed
This is the biggest impact. Both your test methods using `[ExpectedException(typeof(...))]` will fail to compile. Replace with `Assert.ThrowsExactly<T>()`:

```csharp
// Before
[ExpectedException(typeof(ArgumentNullException))]
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_NullInput_ThrowsArgumentNull()
{
    Validate(null);
}

// After
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_NullInput_ThrowsArgumentNull()
{
    Assert.ThrowsExactly<ArgumentNullException>(() => Validate(null));
}
```

### 2. `Assert.IsTrue(true)` triggers warning MSTEST0032
Severity was escalated from Info → **Warning** in v4. Your `Validate_ValidInput_Succeeds` test will produce a build warning about an always-true assertion.

### Other v4 breaking changes (not hitting your code, but good to know):
- `TestMethodAttribute.Execute` → `ExecuteAsync` (if you have custom attributes)
- `ClassCleanupBehavior` enum removed
- `TestContext.Properties` changed to `IDictionary<string, object>`
- `Assert` APIs no longer accept `message` + `params object[]` (use interpolation)
- .NET < 8.0 support dropped (you're fine on net8.0)

Full migration guide: https://learn.microsoft.com/dotnet/core/testing/unit-testing-mstest-migration-v3-v4

Would you like me to apply these fixes and upgrade the project?
